    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-03-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-03-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="622"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d622">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/1076.</note>
                <head>[Untitled]</head>
                <p>Referring to the memorandum of the Embassy of Mexico, of the 20th instant,
                    requesting that appropriate instructions be issued to the United States attorney
                    for Arizona concerning the hearing involving certain persons accused of having
                    crossed the international boundary and attacked Saric and other places in
                    Mexico, the Department of State has the honor to inform the embassy that it is
                    advised by a letter of the 25th instant from the Department of Justice, to which
                    the correspondence was communicated, that copies thereof have been forwarded to
                    the United States attorney for Arizona for consideration and such action, if
                    any, as may be practicable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-03-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 31, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
